<title type="html"><![CDATA[What Is The Correct Opinion Concerning Al-Hajjaj Ibn Yoosuf Ath-Thaqafee? Is He A Disbeliever?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1332&amp;p=1416#p1416"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">What Is The Correct Opinion Concerning Al-Hajjaj Ibn Yoosuf Ath-Thaqafee? Is He A Disbeliever?</span></strong><br /><br />From:  Fataawaa of Shaikh Al-Albaanee (Rahimahullah)<br /> <br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Question:</span></strong> <br />What is the correct opinion concerning Al-Hajjaj Ibn Yoosuf Ath-Thaqafee? Is he a disbeliever?<br /> <br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Answer:</span></strong><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">We bear witness that Al-Hajjaj was an evildoer, an oppressor.</span></strong> However, we do not know from him that he rejected any of those aspects from the Religion, which one is required to know by necessity.<br /><br />Therefore, <strong><span style="color: #0000FF">it is not permissible to declare him a disbeliever</span></strong> just on the basis that he used to commit evil, oppress others and kill innocent Muslims.<br /><br /><em>[Al-Asaalah, Issue #1]</em><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> â€” Fri Mar 24, 2017 10:04 pm</p><hr />
